	<Title>
		Know how to do a proper push-up?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Strength training includes exercises using your own body weight for resistance. Push-ups, for example, work your chest, arms, shoulders and upper body. Position yourself on your hands and feet with your eyes facing the floor. Place your hands slightly greater than shoulder-width apart and your feet comfortably apart. Keeping your back and legs straight, slowly bend your elbows and lower your chest until your chin reaches the ground. You&apos;ll feel tension in the muscles in your back, abdomen and upper arms. Then slowly return to the starting position. Repeat.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
